This paper is about image segmentation using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses methods for dealing with data imbalance, which is a common problem in machine learning, suggesting that it could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function for training neural networks, which could be of interest to the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper focuses on medical imaging applications, which could make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
